"{\"abstract\":\"The semantics of computational systems (e.g., relational and knowledge data bases, query-answering systems, programming languages, etc.) can often be expressed as (the specification of) a logical theory Th. Queries, goals, and claims about the behavior or features of the system can be expressed as formulas \\u03c6 which should be checked with respect to the intended model of Th, which is often huge or even incomputable. In this paper we show how to prove such semantic properties \\u03c6 of Th by just finding a model A of Th \\u222a {\\u03c6} \\u222a Z\\u03c6, where Z\\u03c6 is an appropriate (possibly empty) theory depending on \\u03c6 only. Applications to relational and deductive databases, rewriting-based systems, logic programming, and answer set programming are discussed.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"1745692\",\"name\":\"Salvador Lucas\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1745692\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[],\"corpusId\":220480929,\"doi\":\"10.24963/ijcai.2020/710\",\"fieldsOfStudy\":[\"Computer Science\"],\"influentialCitationCount\":0,\"is_open_access\":false,\"is_publisher_licensed\":false,\"paperId\":\"12f4af429d745f1459f922ef10b6be16e441c88b\",\"references\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":null,\"name\":\"Sun Kim\"},{\"authorId\":\"34150749\",\"name\":\"H. Zhang\"}],\"doi\":null,\"intent\":[],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"2bde7aa703f3bbd05a677bc2a1d7d1f2a5b6d625\",\"title\":\"ModGen: Theorem Proving by Model Generation\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/2bde7aa703f3bbd05a677bc2a1d7d1f2a5b6d625\",\"venue\":\"AAAI\",\"year\":1994},{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":null,\"name\":\"Jean Goubault-Larrecq. Finite models for formal securit proofs\"}],\"doi\":null,\"intent\":[\"methodology\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"\",\"title\":\"Journal of Computer Security\",\"url\":\"\",\"venue\":\"18(6):1247\\u20131299,\",\"year\":2010},{\"arxivId\":n